SciHub to PDF
=============

Downloads PDFs by DOI, article title, arXiv id, or a BibTeX file, using
Sci-Hub, Libgen, and arXiv.

Modernized fork of `bibcure/scihub2pdf
<https://github.com/bibcure/scihub2pdf>`__, updated to run on a current
Python / Selenium stack:

- The Sci-Hub backend now drives headless Google Chrome via Selenium 4. The
  original PhantomJS backend no longer works (PhantomJS was removed from
  Selenium 4).
- Multiple Sci-Hub mirrors are tried in order, skipping unreachable ones.
- Installs cleanly on Windows with a real ``scihub2pdf`` command.

Requirements
------------

- Python 3.8+
- Google Chrome (only for the Sci-Hub backend; Selenium Manager downloads a
  matching driver automatically).

Install
-------

Using uv (recommended)::

    git clone https://github.com/zegran/scihubpdf.git
    cd scihubpdf
    uv venv
    uv pip install -e .

Or with pip::

    git clone https://github.com/zegran/scihubpdf.git
    cd scihubpdf
    pip install -e .

Features and how to use
-----------------------

Given a bibtex file::

    $ scihub2pdf -i input.bib

Given a DOI number::

    $ scihub2pdf 10.1038/s41524-017-0032-0

Given a title::

    $ scihub2pdf --title An useful paper

Arxiv::

    $ scihub2pdf arxiv:0901.2686
    $ scihub2pdf --title arxiv:Periodic table for topological insulators

Location folder as argument (``-l`` is a folder prefix, not a file path)::

    $ scihub2pdf -i input.bib -l somefolder/

Use libgen instead sci-hub::

    $ scihub2pdf -i input.bib --uselibgen

Output location
---------------

By default each run writes its PDFs into a timestamped subfolder
(``<base>/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS/``) so downloads from different sessions stay
separated. ``<base>`` is the ``-l`` value, or the current directory when
``-l`` is omitted. Pass ``--no-session-dir`` to write straight into the base
folder (the legacy behaviour)::

    $ scihub2pdf 10.1016/j.cell.2017.05.016 -l papers/ --no-session-dir

Sci-Hub mirrors
---------------

The Sci-Hub backend tries these mirrors in order, skips unreachable ones, and
stops at the first that serves the PDF::

    sci-hub.st -> sci-hub.ist -> sci-hub.ru -> sci-hub.se

Override with the SCIHUB_MIRROR environment variable (single mirror or a
comma-separated list)::

    SCIHUB_MIRROR="https://sci-hub.ist/" scihub2pdf 10.1016/j.cell.2017.05.016 -l papers/

Download from list of items
---------------------------

Given a text file of DOIs::

    10.1038/s41524-017-0032-0
    10.1063/1.3149495

download all pdf's::

    $ scihub2pdf -i dois.txt --txt

Given a text file of titles::

    Some Title 1
    Some Title 2

download all pdf's::

    $ scihub2pdf -i titles.txt --txt --title

Given a text file of arXiv ids::

    arXiv:1708.06891
    arXiv:1708.06071

download all pdf's::

    $ scihub2pdf -i arxiv_ids.txt --txt

